SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 160.13A of Title 17, unless
14
15
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. Prior to commencing construction of a wind energy facility,
16
17
the owner or operator of a wind energy facility shall file a surety
17
18
bond with the Secretary of State in the sum of One Hundred Thousand
18
19
Dollars ($100,000.00) and such bond shall be conditioned upon
19
20
compliance with the Oklahoma Wind Energy Development Act for payment
20
21
of any location damages due which the owner or operator cannot
21
22
otherwise pay. The Secretary of State shall hold such corporate
22
23
surety bond for the benefit of the landowners of this state and
23
24
shall ensure that such security is in a form readily payable to a
24
