1
landowner awarded damages in an action brought pursuant to this act.
1
2
Each corporate surety bond filed with the Secretary of State shall
2
3
be accompanied by a filing fee of Ten Dollars ($10.00).
3
4
B. The bonding company shall file, for such fee as is provided
4
5
for by law, a certificate that such bond is in effect or has been
5
6
canceled, or that a claim has been made against it in the office of
6
7
the court clerk in each county in which the owner or operator is
7
8
planning to construct. The bond must remain in full force and
8
9
effect as long as the owner or operator continues wind energy
9
10
operations in this state. Each such filing shall be accompanied by
10
11
a filing fee of Ten Dollars ($10.00).
11
12
C. Upon deposit of the bond, the owner or operator shall be
12
13
permitted entry upon the property and shall be permitted to commence
13
14
construction of a wind energy facility in accordance with the terms
14
15
and conditions of any lease or other existing contractual or lawful
15
16
right.
16
17
D. If the damages agreed to by the parties or awarded by the
17
18
court are greater than the bond, the owner or operator shall pay the
18
19
damages immediately or post an additional bond sufficient to cover
19
20
the damages. Such increase in bond shall comply with the
20
21
requirements of this section.
